# eTalk UI aesthetics (portable design language)

Use this when building or changing UI so new screens match the established **light education** look. You may copy this rule into other apps to keep the same visual DNA.

## Brand feel

- **Education-first**: calm, trustworthy, readable—never flashy or “startup neon.”
- **Milk white paper**: base `#faf9f7` with a soft warm gradient—no strong blue page washes; blue→cyan is for logo, CTAs, and links only.
- **Dual accent**: **slate ink** (structure, body text) + **electric blue** `#0066FF` → **cyan** `#00D4FF` / `#38BDF8` (CTAs, links, decor, accent lines). Logo on **light header** like [SpeakX](https://speakx.ai/)—no dark plates; prefer transparent PNG/SVG.
- **Seamless sections**: gradient fades and **hairline** separators; avoid heavy boxed panels unless content truly needs a card.
- **Cultural decor** (line art): **low opacity**, **blue** tint (`#3b82f6`)—ambient only; must not compete with copy.

## Color schema (CSS tokens)

Map these in `:root` / `@theme` when porting:

| Role | Typical use |
|------|----------------|
| `--background` / `--etalk-bg-paper` | `#faf9f7` milk white |
| `--foreground` | Dark ink `#2a2f38` |
| `--brand-navy` / `--brand-navy-deep` | `#1e293b` / `#0f172a` headings, body emphasis |
| `--brand-blue` / `--brand-blue-cyan` | `#0066FF` / `#00D4FF` accents, CTAs, gradients |
| `--brand-muted` | Secondary body `#5c6570` |
| `--surface-elevated` | `#ffffff` cards on paper |
| `--surface-subtle` | `#eeede8` secondary surfaces |
| `--hairline` | `rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.08)` borders/dividers |

**Page background**: milk white (`--etalk-bg-layers` warm gradient). Optional whisper of blue in decor only—not sitewide blue fills.

## Typography

- **Headings / wordmark**: `.etalk-wordmark` / `.etalk-text-brand-gradient` = **blue→cyan** gradient (logo), not gold.
- **English UI**: rounded humanist sans (e.g. Baloo Thambi 2).
- **Odia**: Noto Sans Oriya + paired Latin sans when `lang-or`.
- **Hierarchy**: eyebrow (muted) → H1 (ink) → **blue** accent line → body (muted).

## Components & surfaces

- **Primary CTA** (`.etalk-btn-gold` / `.etalk-btn-primary`): **blue→cyan** gradient, white label, soft blue shadow—no gold/metallic fill.
- **Secondary actions**: white/outline on paper, `border-[var(--hairline)]`, hover **blue** border tint (`#f8fbff` wash).
- **Feature tiles**: white card, hairline border, hover lift + **blue** edge glow—not gold or yellow shadow.
- **FAQ**: hairline rows, light hover wash.
- **Header**: frosted cool paper + blur; border `--hairline`.

## Motion & hero

- **Particles / canvas**: subtle network in **blue** tones; must not reduce legibility on mobile.
- **Decor SVGs**: low opacity blue line art.
- Respect **`prefers-reduced-motion`**.

## Ethics & a11y

- **Content over chrome**: lower decor opacity before lowering text contrast.
- **Focus**: visible **blue** focus ring with sensible offset.
- **Contrast**: body text on paper meets readable contrast; gradient text for short accents only.

## Porting to another app

1. Copy the token block and **layered** `body` background (`--etalk-blue-pattern`).
2. Keep one humanist sans + display/rounded heading style.
3. Reuse **blue CTA + ink typography**—never reintroduce gold separators or amber quote glows.
4. Apply hairlines and soft **blue-tinted** shadows instead of warm/yellow halos.
5. Test ambient graphics at **375px** width first.
